Interface ResultReceived<S,O>

  • Type Parameters:
    S - The type of the source of the result.
    O - The type of the result.

    public interface ResultReceived<S,O>
    Represents a handler of a received result. This interface is intended to be used for results which may not be returned immediately. APIs using this interface will remove the reference to the object after calling it once. This means you must re-register it to receive another notification of receiving data.
    Author:
    Glen Husman
